## Adjusting During Play

If the conflict feels too easy:
- Reinforcements arrive (makes narrative sense)
- Enemy reveals hidden capability (was holding back)
- Environmental complication (alarm, collapse, hazard)
- Objective shifts (villain escapes with the prize)

If the conflict feels too hard:
- NPC ally arrives (someone who'd realistically help)
- Enemy offers terms (most people prefer living)
- Environmental opportunity (escape route, cover, weapon)
- Reveal a weakness (crack in armor, old injury, fear)

Make adjustments for story and drama, not mathematical balance.

